# Frontend Conventions

## Component Architecture

- **Functional components only** — no class components
- **State colocation** — keep state in the component that owns it; lift only when shared
- **Props interfaces** — define inline or named interface above the component

```typescript
interface MyComponentProps {
  activeAddress: string | null;
  onAction: (id: string) => void;
}

const MyComponent: React.FC<MyComponentProps> = ({ activeAddress, onAction }) => { ... };
export default MyComponent;
```

## Routing

`App.tsx` → `BrowserRouter` → `Home.tsx` handles nested routes:
- `/` → HeroSection, `/builder` → WorkflowBuilder, `/marketplace` → Marketplace
- `/market` → MarketDataPanel, `/saved` → SavedWorkflows, `/ai` → AIPage
- `/approve/:token` → ApproveExecution (separate from Home)

Add new pages in `Home.tsx` route switch + `Navbar` links.

## Styling

**Custom CSS with CSS variables** in `src/styles/App.css`. No Tailwind.

```css
/* Use existing CSS variables */
var(--color-bg), var(--color-text), var(--color-primary), var(--color-border)
var(--radius-md), var(--text-sm), var(--text-xs)
```

Utility classes available: `.card`, `.btn`, `.btn-primary`, `.btn-outline`, `.btn-ghost`,
`.text-sm`, `.text-xs`, `.text-muted`, `.font-bold`, `.animate-fadeIn`

Prefer CSS classes over inline styles for new components. Inline styles exist in older
components but should not be the pattern going forward.

## API Client

All server calls go through `src/services/api.ts`. Add new endpoints there:

```typescript
export const api = {
  myNewEndpoint: async (param: string): Promise<ResponseType> => {
    const res = await fetch(`${BASE_URL}/my-endpoint`, { ... });
    return readJsonOrThrow<ResponseType>(res);
  },
};
```

`BASE_URL` defaults to `http://localhost:8080/api` (configurable via `VITE_API_BASE_URL`).

## Wallet Access

```typescript
import { useWallet } from '@txnlab/use-wallet-react';
const { activeAddress, transactionSigner } = useWallet();
```

Always null-check `activeAddress` before wallet-dependent operations.

## Node Definitions

All workflow block types are defined in `src/services/nodeDefinitions.ts`.
To add a new block type, add an entry to `NODE_DEFINITIONS` array with:
`type`, `label`, `category`, `icon`, `color`, `description`, `configFields[]`.
